{"title_page": "Star\u00fd Tekov", "text_new": "[[Image:Okres levice.png|thumb|right|300px|Location of [[Levice District]] in the [[Nitra Region]]]]\n\n'''Star\u00fd Tekov''' ({{lang-de|italic=yes|Bersenberg}}, also ''Altbarsch, Altbersenberg, (Alt-)Bersenburg'', in earlier times also ''Berschenberg'', Alt ''Berschenburg'', {{lang-hu|\u00d3bars}}) is a [[village]] and [[municipality]] in the [[Levice District]] in the [[Nitra Region]] of [[Slovakia]].\n\n==History==\nIn [[history|historical records]] the village was first mentioned in 1075.\n\n==Geography==\nThe [[village]] lies at an [[altitude]] of 176 metres and covers an [[area]] of {{convert|10.573|km\u00b2|0|abbr=on}}. It has a [[population]] of about 1470 people.\n\n==Ethnicity==\nThe village is approximately 87% [[Slovaks|Slovak]] and 13% [[Hungarian people|Magyar]].\n\n==Facilities==\nThe village has a public [[library]] a [[gym]] and [[Association football pitch|football pitch]].\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.starytekov.sk Obecna stranka]\n\n{{Levice District}}\n\n{{coord|48|15|N|18|32|E|region:SK_type:city|display=title}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stary Tekov}}\n[[Category:Villages and municipalities in Levice District]]\n\n\n{{Levice-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "[[Image:Okres levice.png|thumb|right|300px|Location of [[Levice District]] in the [[Nitra Region]]]]\n\n'''Star\u00fd Tekov''' ({{lang-de|italic=yes|Bersenberg}}, also ''Altbarsch, Altbersenberg, (Alt-)Bersenburg'', in earlier times also ''Berschenberg'', Alt ''Berschenburg'', {{lang-hu|\u00d3bars}}) is a [[village]] and [[municipality]] in the [[Levice District]] in the [[Nitra Region]] of [[Slovakia]].\n\n==History==\nIn [[history|historical records]] the village was first mentioned in 1075.\n\n==Geography==\nThe [[village]] lies at an [[altitude]] of 176 metres and covers an [[area]] of {{convert|10.573|km\u00b2|0|abbr=on}}. It has a [[population]] of about 1470 people.\n\n==Ethnicity==\nThe village is approximately 87% [[Slovaks|Slovak]] and 13% [[Hungarian people|Magyar]].\n\n==Facilities==\nThe village has a public [[library]] a [[gym]] and [[Association football pitch|football pitch]].\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.starytekov.sk Obecna stranka]\n\n{{Levice District}}\n\n{{coord|48|15|N|18|32|E|region:SK_type:city|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stary Tekov}}\n[[Category:Villages and municipalities in Levice District]]\n\n\n{{Levice-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star%C3%BD_Tekov"}
{"title_page": "Star\u00fd Poddvorov", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name=Star\u00fd Poddvorov\n|settlement_type=Municipality and village\n|image_skyline=Vetrny mlyn Stary Poddvorov.jpg\n|image_caption = Wind mill from 1870, a Cultural Monument of the Czech Republic\n|image_shield=Star\u00fd Poddvorov CoA CZ.jpg\n|image_flag=Star\u00fd Poddvorov flag CZ.jpg\n|subdivision_type=Country\n|subdivision_name={{CZE}}\n|subdivision_type1=[[Regions of the Czech Republic|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1=[[South Moravian Region|South Moravian]]\n|subdivision_type2=[[Districts of the Czech Republic|District]]\n|subdivision_name2=[[Hodon\u00edn District|Hodon\u00edn]]\n|coordinates = {{coord|48|52|26|N|16|59|6|E|region:CZ|display=inline,title}}\n|pushpin_map=Czech Republic|area_total_km2=5.45\n|population_total=980\n|population_as_of=1.1.2012\n|population_density_km2=auto\n|elevation_m=224\n|postal_code_type=Postal&nbsp;code|postal_code=696&nbsp;16 to 696&nbsp;17\n|website=http://poddvorov.cz\n}}\n\n'''Star\u00fd Poddvorov''' is a village and municipality (''[[obec]]'') in [[Hodon\u00edn District]] in the [[South Moravian Region]] of the Czech Republic.\n\nThe municipality covers an area of {{convert|5.45|km2|sqmi}}, and has a population of 969 (as at 1&nbsp;January 2008).\n\nStar\u00fd Poddvorov lies approximately {{convert|12|km|mi|0}} west of [[Hodon\u00edn]], {{convert|46|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-east of [[Brno]], and {{convert|230|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-east of [[Prague]].\n\n==Twin towns \u2014 sister cities==\n{{See also|List of twin towns and sister cities in the Czech Republic}}\n\nStar\u00fd Poddvorov is a member of the ''Charter of European Rural Communities'', a [[town twinning]] association across the [[European Union]], alongside with:<ref>{{cite web |title=Charter members|url=https://www.europeancharter.eu/chartermembers/|website=europeancharter.eu|publisher=Charter of European Rural Communities|accessdate=2019-09-07}}</ref>\n{{div col|colwidth=20em}}\n*{{flagicon|SPA}} [[Bienvenida, Badajoz|Bienvenida]], Spain\n*{{flagicon|BEL}} [[Bi\u00e8vre, Belgium|Bi\u00e8vre]], Belgium\n*{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Bucine]], Italy\n*{{flagicon|IRL}} [[Cashel, County Tipperary|Cashel]], Ireland\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Ciss\u00e9, Vienne|Ciss\u00e9]], France\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Desborough]], England, United Kingdom\n*{{flagicon|NED}} [[Esch, Netherlands|Esch]], Netherlands\n*{{flagicon|GER}} [[Hepstedt]], Germany\n*{{flagicon|ROM}} [[Ib\u0103ne\u0219ti, Mure\u0219|Ib\u0103ne\u0219ti]], Romania\n*{{flagicon|LAT}} [[Kandava Municipality|Kandava]], Latvia\n*{{flagicon|FIN}} [[Kannus]], Finland\n*{{flagicon|GRC}} [[Kolindros]], Greece\n*{{flagicon|AUT}} [[Lassee]], Austria\n*{{flagicon|SVK}} [[Medzev]], Slovakia\n*{{flagicon|SLO}} [[Morav\u010de]], Slovenia\n*{{flagicon|DEN}} [[N\u00e6stved]], Denmark\n*{{flagicon|HUN}} [[Nagycenk]], Hungary\n*{{flagicon|MLT}} [[Nadur]], Malta\n*{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Ockelbo Municipality|Ockelbo]], Sweden\n*{{flagicon|CYP}} [[Pano Lefkara]], Cyprus\n*{{flagicon|EST}} [[P\u00f5lva Parish|P\u00f5lva]], Estonia\n*{{flagicon|POR}} [[Samuel, Portugal|Samuel]], Portugal\n*{{flagicon|BUL}} [[Slivo Pole]], Bulgaria\n*{{flagicon|POL}} [[Gmina Strzy\u017c\u00f3w|Strzy\u017c\u00f3w]], Poland\n*{{flagicon|CRO}} [[Tisno]], Croatia\n*{{flagicon|LUX}} [[Troisvierges]], Luxembourg\n*{{flagicon|LTU}} [[\u017dagar\u0117]], Lithuania\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Star\u00fd Poddvorov}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080829122009/http://www.czso.cz/lexikon/mos_vdb.nsf/okresy/CZ0625/ Czech Statistical Office: Municipalities of Hodon\u00edn District]\n\n{{Hodon\u00edn District}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stary Poddvorov}}\n[[Category:Villages in Hodon\u00edn District]]\n[[Category:Moravian Slovakia]]\n\n\n{{SouthMoravia-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name=Star\u00fd Poddvorov\n|settlement_type=Municipality and village\n|image_skyline=Vetrny mlyn Stary Poddvorov.jpg\n|image_caption = Wind mill from 1870, a Cultural Monument of the Czech Republic\n|image_shield=Star\u00fd Poddvorov CoA CZ.jpg\n|image_flag=Star\u00fd Poddvorov flag CZ.jpg\n|subdivision_type=Country\n|subdivision_name={{CZE}}\n|subdivision_type1=[[Regions of the Czech Republic|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1=[[South Moravian Region|South Moravian]]\n|subdivision_type2=[[Districts of the Czech Republic|District]]\n|subdivision_name2=[[Hodon\u00edn District|Hodon\u00edn]]\n|coordinates = {{coord|48|52|26|N|16|59|6|E|region:CZ|display=inline,title}}\n|pushpin_map=Czech Republic|area_total_km2=5.45\n|population_total=980\n|population_as_of=1.1.2012\n|population_density_km2=auto\n|elevation_m=224\n|postal_code_type=Postal&nbsp;code|postal_code=696&nbsp;16 to 696&nbsp;17\n|website=http://poddvorov.cz\n}}\n\n'''Star\u00fd Poddvorov''' is a village and municipality (''[[obec]]'') in [[Hodon\u00edn District]] in the [[South Moravian Region]] of the Czech Republic.\n\nThe municipality covers an area of {{convert|5.45|km2|sqmi}}, and has a population of 969 (as at 1&nbsp;January 2008).\n\nStar\u00fd Poddvorov lies approximately {{convert|12|km|mi|0}} west of [[Hodon\u00edn]], {{convert|46|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-east of [[Brno]], and {{convert|230|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-east of [[Prague]].\n\n==Twin towns \u2014 sister cities==\n{{See also|List of twin towns and sister cities in the Czech Republic}}\n\nStar\u00fd Poddvorov is a member of the ''Charter of European Rural Communities'', a [[town twinning]] association across the [[European Union]], alongside with:<ref>{{cite web |title=Charter members|url=https://www.europeancharter.eu/chartermembers/|website=europeancharter.eu|publisher=Charter of European Rural Communities|accessdate=2019-09-07}}</ref>\n{{div col|colwidth=20em}}\n*{{flagicon|SPA}} [[Bienvenida, Badajoz|Bienvenida]], Spain\n*{{flagicon|BEL}} [[Bi\u00e8vre, Belgium|Bi\u00e8vre]], Belgium\n*{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Bucine]], Italy\n*{{flagicon|IRL